2026-03-30 15:54:14,115 [INFO] ARSS: [Advanced] Recommend sources session_id=f3de1b4e-3931-44af-8f6e-ecea06d861e1 chapter=1 option_id=option-3 query=Artificial Intelligence Applications in Higher Education: A Comprehensive Literature Review From E-Learning to AI Integration: Historical Context and Adoption Drivers This brief focuses on the 'why' behind the technological shift. Starting with the baseline of standard e-learning tools, the chapter should analyze the specific pedagogical, economic, and institutional pressures that necessitated a move toward AI. It should end with a detailed categorization of adoption drivers, such as the demand for 24/7 student support, administrative efficiency, and the post-pandemic acceleration of digital-first strategies. Establish the historical and current context of AI adoption in HE. Literature Review Organize the chapter by analyzing the three specific spheres of influence mentioned in the brief: pedagogical, economic, and institutional. Start with the pedagogical shift—moving from one-size-fits-all E-learning to adaptive AI pathways. Move to economic and institutional pressures, such as the need for administrative efficiency and cost-effective 24/7 support systems. Use these pressures to bridge the gap between historical E-learning and current AI integration. End the chapter by categorizing these pressures into a definitive taxonomy of adoption drivers (e.g., Efficiency, Scalability, and Personalization). open access scholarly article
